    <string name="help_overview_content">HAMGIS is a complete geographic measurement system consisting of watch and phone components.</string>
    <string name="help_watch_content">Watch app supports two working modes:\n\n1. Area Measurement Mode: Focused on farmland measurement, automatically calculates area and perimeter\n2. GIS Collection Mode: Professional version, can collect point, line, and polygon features simultaneously\n\nOperations:\n- Short press \"Collect\": Collect point\n- Short press \"Finish\": Complete current feature\n- Long press \"Finish\": Complete entire GIS project</string>
    <string name="help_phone_content">Phone app serves as data reception and export center:\n\n1. Ensure Zepp App is running in background\n2. Phone automatically receives data after watch sends it\n3. Supports export to CSV, GeoJSON, KML, JSON formats\n4. JSON format optimized with complete project information</string>
    <string name="help_export_content">Export format descriptions:\n\nCSV: Suitable for Excel viewing, includes project summary\nGeoJSON: Standard GIS format, supports ArcGIS, QGIS and other software\nKML: Google Earth format, includes coordinates and attributes\nJSON: Complete project data with formatted display</string>
    <string name="help_modes_content">Mode switching:\n\nIn watch settings, you can switch application mode:\n- Area Measurement Mode: Suitable for quick farmland measurement\n- GIS Collection Mode: Suitable for professional field collection, one project can contain multiple feature types</string>
    <string name="help_data_sync_content">Data sync workflow:\n\n1. Watch measurement â†’ Click \"Export to Android\"\n2. Wait for phone to receive data (approximately 5-30 seconds)\n3. Phone displays data preview\n4. Select export format\n5. Select save location\n6. File saved successfully</string>
    <string name="help_troubleshooting_content">Common issues:\n\nQ: Data not received?\nA: Check if Zepp App is running in background, ensure watch and phone connection is normal\n\nQ: Export failed?\nA: Ensure data format is correct, try resending data\n\nQ: JSON export format error?\nA: JSON formatting issue fixed, ensure exported JSON is valid</string>
